<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-14T18:03:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-14T18:03:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/9–1354: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d549fn1">Drafted by the Deputy Director of the Office of
                                <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Political and Security Affairs
                                (<persName>Bond</persName>), cleared by the Bureau of Far Eastern
                            Affairs and the Bureau of European Affairs, and signed by Assistant
                            Secretary <persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName>.</note></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">official use only</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-14T19:03:00-04:00">September 14,
                                1954—7:03 p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>146. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 229 re Chinese representation.
                        Department accepts moratorium formula proposed by <persName corresp="#p_DIXONSPJ1">Dixon</persName> but would prefer use phrase
                        “during the current year” instead of “during 1954”. Please so inform
                            <persName corresp="#p_DIXONSPJ1">Dixon</persName>. If British unwilling
                        accept this change you are authorized inform <persName corresp="#p_DIXONSPJ1">Dixon</persName> we agree to formula as set forth
                            <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>